iwts_performer:754 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Desiree Dorion";
  schema:description """Desiree Dorion has had multiple songs chart in the top 100 on the Canadian country music charts, along with reaching the top spot on the Indigenous Music Countdown. The JUNO nominee released her 7th album, “Remember Your Name,” on September 20th, 2024 which has amassed over 100,000 global streams to date. It reached the top 20 on the national Earshot charts across all genres and top 10 on the national Earshot folk/roots/blues charts.

Desiree is a member of the Opaskwayak Cree Nation.""";
