  schema:name "Vox Britannia - The Best of British Rock N Roll";
  schema:description "Vox Britannia–The Best of British Rock N Roll is a smashing tribute to England’s greatest bands from the 60’s-80’s with electrifying iconic hits from artists such as Led Zeppelin, The Who, Rolling Stones, Queen, Bowie, Elton John, The Cure, The Smiths, The Jam, etc. The band’s an all-star lineup: Tim Smith (Sheryl Crow), Jim Stapley (Kenney Jones & Ron Wood Band, Yola),  Lawrence Katz (Mighty Mighty Bosstones), Richard Sherrington (Jill Scott, Noel Gallagher’s High Flying Birds), & Erik Aylesworth (CeeLo). They’re an ace band with a wicked show";
